+Question:
+
+For mission `exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit`, step `step-007`, identify
+the strongest local repository materials for freezing the single witness-local
+branch around `F_SS(1/12)` without reopening packet semantics, the Step-6
+authority sheets, or the discarded itinerary scorecard.
+
+The inherited branch commitments are fixed:
+
+- the witness to freeze is the single carried witness `F_SS(1/12)`, not the
+  family `F_SS(mu)`;
+- the controlling hard gates are only the repaired Step-6 sheets
+  `G_tmpl(P_n; I) = (Delta_tmpl, Delta_spec)` with
+  `Delta_tmpl <= 1/4`, `Delta_spec <= 49/256`,
+  and
+  `G_leak(P_n; I) = (L_tot, L_mirror, L_companion, L_feedback, L_cross)` with
+  repaired budget vector
+  `(1/4, 1/12, 1/12, 1/16, 1/24)`;
+- earlier threshold drift, especially any leakage-side `L_cross` mismatch,
+  must be treated as historical record variance only, not as a live branch
+  choice;
+- all later leakage comparisons must stay in one frozen same-currency
+  protocol;
+- `t_clk`, `t_trig`, `t_rot`, and `t_next` may be recorded only as secondary
+  diagnostics, not as promoted pass/fail gates; and
+- no discretionary repair is allowed:
+  no extra bridge,
+  no shell-locked mode,
+  no post hoc companion,
+  no witness swap,
+  no threshold retuning,
+  and no alternate bookkeeping currency unless later exact closure itself
+  forces bookkeeping additions, in which case that belongs to Step 2 rather
+  than Step-1 rescue logic.
+
+Return concrete findings, not just file paths, on these exact questions:
+
+1. Which local materials most sharply identify the exact object on the
+   canonical one-bridge role-labeled ledger that this branch should call
+   `F_SS(1/12)`?
+   Include:
+   normalization,
+   packet semantics,
+   mandatory conjugate completion,
+   fixed window `I = [0, 1]`,
+   carried sign / phase / role conventions,
+   and any exact statement of what data are already frozen versus reserved for
+   later closure-forced bookkeeping only.
+2. Which local materials are the strongest authority sources for the repaired
+   Step-6 `G_tmpl` and `G_leak` sheets that Step 7 must inherit?
+   Identify the most authoritative local source path for each threshold sheet.
+3. Where exactly does the local record show earlier threshold drift,
+   especially the leakage-side `L_cross` mismatch?
+   State the earlier conflicting value and which later source resolves it.
+4. Which local materials best justify one explicit same-currency rule for all
+   later gate comparisons on this branch?
+   State the strongest honest formulation supported by the record.
+5. Which local materials most clearly support the diagnostics-only status of
+   `t_clk`, `t_trig`, `t_rot`, and `t_next`, and the rejection of descriptive
+   stage-order narrative as a hard scorecard?
+6. Which local materials most clearly support the no-repair and no-overclaim
+   guardrail?
+   Distinguish:
+   closure-forced bookkeeping that later Step 2 may record,
+   versus illegitimate rescue or scope drift.
+7. Based on the local record alone, is Chain Step 2 now well-posed after this
+   Step-1 freeze?
+   If yes, list the exact frozen commitments Step 2 must inherit.
+   If no, name the sharpest witness-freeze or authority-sheet failure.
+8. What is the minimum honest Step-7 exploration split?
+   Is two explorations enough:
+   one witness/authority freeze and one guardrail/verdict synthesis,
+   or does the local record force a third exploration?
+
+Please prefer local materials that let later explorations cite exact files for:
+
+- the canonical witness packet sheet for `F_SS(1/12)`;
+- the fixed normalization, role labels, sign sheet, phase anchor, and window;
+- the controlling repaired `G_tmpl` and `G_leak` authority sheets;
+- the historical `L_cross` drift record and its later resolution;
+- the same-currency bookkeeping rule;
+- the diagnostics-only status of itinerary/timing quantities;
+- the no-repair and no-overclaim rule; and
+- the Step-2-readiness verdict.
