+## Honest Scorecard Memo
+
+### Hard Pass / Fail Gates
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The only hard gates frozen for this branch are the repaired
+  Step-6 sheets:
+
+  ```text
+  G_tmpl(P_n; I) = (Delta_tmpl, Delta_spec)
+  with
+  Delta_tmpl <= 1/4,
+  Delta_spec <= 49/256
+  ```
+
+  and
+
+  ```text
+  G_leak(P_n; I)
+    = (L_tot, L_mirror, L_companion, L_feedback, L_cross)
+  with
+  (L_tot, L_mirror, L_companion, L_feedback, L_cross)
+    <= (1/4, 1/12, 1/12, 1/16, 1/24).
+  ```
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The Step-6 freeze keeps those two objects distinct and promoted
+  unchanged.
+  Step 7 does not collapse them into one conjunction gate and does not add any
+  third scorecard.
+- `[INFERRED]` Later Step-2 and Step-3 work must inherit these gates exactly on
+  the same canonical packet sheet and same frozen same-currency protocol.
+
+### Secondary Diagnostics Only
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The branch planning handoff explicitly demotes
+  `t_clk`,
+  `t_trig`,
+  `t_rot`,
+  and
+  `t_next`
+  to secondary diagnostics only.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The discarded itinerary route stays discarded:
+  `pre-trigger delay filter`
+  remains
+  `not useful for the target theorem or counterexample question`,
+  and
+  `next-stage transfer-start filter`
+  remains
+  `not well-defined`.
+- `[INFERRED]` Honest Step-7 formulation:
+  any later record of stage order, event times, or descriptive transfer
+  narrative is admissible only as secondary evidence.
+  None of it may be promoted back into pass/fail language.
+
+### Static Dossier Versus Dynamic Pass
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The Step-4 / Step-6 dossier shows only that `F_SS(1/12)` is a
+  recorded friendly static witness on the frozen sheet.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The run-002 winning chain and judgment explicitly separate this
+  from later exact closure and exact dynamic survival.
+- `[INFERRED]` Therefore a Step-1 dossier pass is **not** yet an exact dynamic
+  pass.
+  Step 7 may freeze the witness and scorecard only.
+  It may not claim closure, finite exact isolability, dynamic survival, or
+  near-circuit behavior.
+
+## No-Repair Guardrail
+
+### Allowed Later Bookkeeping
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Step 2 may record only content that exact closure itself forces
+  on the already frozen witness and ledger:
+  mandatory conjugates,
+  closure-forced companions,
+  and any additional exact modes or interaction terms that honest closure shows
+  are unavoidable on the same witness.
+- `[INFERRED]` Such additions count as bookkeeping only if they leave all of
+  the following unchanged:
+  the witness identity `F_SS(1/12)`,
+  the canonical packet semantics,
+  the fixed window,
+  the frozen sign / phase / role conventions,
+  and the repaired Step-6 gate sheets.
+
+### Illegitimate Rescue
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The following are disallowed as Step-1 or Step-2 rescue logic:
+  extra bridge,
+  shell-locked mode,
+  post hoc companion not forced by closure,
+  witness swap,
+  threshold retuning,
+  alternate bookkeeping currency,
+  post hoc rephasing,
+  or any revived itinerary scorecard.
+- `[VERIFIED]` The planning judgment is explicit that any added mode is
+  legitimate only if it is already forced by exact closure; otherwise it is a
+  disallowed repair.
+- `[INFERRED]` Class-changing extension is also disallowed:
+  if honest closure exits the audited one-bridge class, that is a constructive
+  failure endpoint, not a license to enlarge the witness.
+
+## No-Overclaim Guardrail
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Strongest claim now allowed:
+  the branch has one frozen witness-local audit problem that is concrete enough
+  to start exact closure bookkeeping on a single named witness under a single
+  authoritative repaired scorecard.
+- `[VERIFIED]` What the local record does **not** yet justify:
+  - exact closure for `F_SS(1/12)`;
+  - a finite exact closed subsystem;
+  - exact dynamic survival on `I = [0, 1]`;
+  - equivalence between `G_tmpl` and `G_leak`;
+  - a family-level theorem about `F_SS(mu)`;
+  - a class-level theorem about the full canonical one-bridge packet class;
+  - a near-circuit counterexample;
+  - or a global obstruction theorem.
+- `[INFERRED]` The branch also may not claim that static friendliness implies
+  eventual dynamic friendliness.
+  That is exactly what later steps must test.
+
+## Step-2 Readiness Verdict
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Chain Step 2 is now well posed.
+- `[INFERRED]` The exact frozen commitments Step 2 must inherit are:
+  1. the single witness `F_SS(1/12)`, not the family `F_SS(mu)`;
+  2. the canonical one-bridge role-labeled helical packet
+     `P_n = (A_n, B_n, C_n, D_n, E_n)`;
+  3. mandatory conjugate completion, one role order, one helical basis choice,
+     one sign sheet, one amplitude anchor, and one phase anchor;
+  4. the shared desired core
+     `A -> B`,
+     `A -> C`,
+     `B,C -> C`,
+     `C,A <-> D`,
+     `D,D -> E`,
+     together with forced spectator classes
+     `mirror`,
+     `companion`,
+     `feedback`,
+     `cross`;
+  5. the fixed normalization
+     `|A_n(0)| = 1`,
+     `arg A_n(0) = 0`,
+     `I = [0, 1]`,
+     `int_I D_on dt = 1`;
+  6. repaired
+     `G_tmpl`
+     and repaired
+     `G_leak`
+     as the only hard pass/fail gates;
+  7. the fixed same-currency rule with the same
+     `D_on` / `D_off`
+     split and same spectator partition;
+  8. itinerary times and stage-order narrative as diagnostics only; and
+  9. the no-repair / no-overclaim guardrail above.
+- `[INFERRED]` No Step-7 kill condition fires:
+  the witness freeze is sharp,
+  the controlling Step-6 authority sheet is concrete once final step-level
+  precedence is honored,
+  hard gates do not need itinerary revival,
+  and the no-repair rule is concrete enough to separate bookkeeping from
+  rescue.
+
+## Outcome
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` Exploration outcome:
+  `succeeded`.
+- `[INFERRED]` The branch now has a clean Step-1 guardrail memo:
+  one honest scorecard,
+  one diagnostics-only demotion for timing language,
+  one no-repair rule,
+  one no-overclaim rule,
+  and one decisive `Step 2 can start` verdict.
